  <!-- LOCAL KNOWLEDGE -->
  <section class="local-section" id="local">
    <h2>Chimney Sweeping in Cranbourne</h2>
    <div class="local-box"><p>Cranbourne is a large outer south-eastern suburb in the City of Casey that has developed across several distinct eras, giving it a more varied housing stock than many outer Melbourne suburbs. The older residential streets around Cranbourne town centre contain homes from the 1960s through the 1980s — a mix of brick veneer homes and weatherboard cottages from the era when Cranbourne was a rural service town on Melbourne's fringe. These older homes very commonly include a single open fireplace or early slow combustion heater as the primary winter heating system, and many of these flue systems have been in use for decades without professional attention. The newer residential estates that expanded rapidly through the 1990s and 2000s brought a different chimney profile: large four and five bedroom homes where slow combustion wood heaters were installed new and have since been used through every winter without a professional service. Cranbourne's flat Westernport plain location means the suburb is fully exposed to cold southerly airflows through winter, and temperatures on the plain can feel significantly colder than the urban heat island further north. Annual chimney cleaning is genuinely important for both the older open fireplaces and the newer slow combustion systems throughout the suburb. We service Cranbourne and the broader Casey south corridor regularly.</p></div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNS -->
  <section class="signs-section" id="signs">
    <h2>Signs Your Cranbourne Chimney Needs Cleaning</h2>
    <ul class="signs-list">
      <li>Smoke backing into the room when the slow combustion heater is first lit in the season</li>
      <li>A smoky smell that persists in the house even when the heater is off</li>
      <li>Slow combustion heater that is hard to get to temperature — restricted flue draw</li>
      <li>A heater or fireplace that has been in regular use without a professional clean</li>
      <li>Visible soot or tar deposits around the heater door or flue collar</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

